FBIS4-32948 "drlat105_a_94019" FBIS-LAT-94-105 Daily Report 25 May 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Pedro Ross Chairs CTC National Secretariat Meeting Pedro Ross Chairs CTC National Secretariat Meeting FL0106002294 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 GMT 25 May 94 FL0106002294 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Spanish BFN [Text] The national secretariat of the Cuban Workers Federation [CTC] has agreed to conduct an in-depth analysis of the causes of the current nationwide shortage of work shoes, and discussed the feasibility of investing the hard currency used by enterprises to buy shoes abroad in national factories. During the meeting, chaired by CTC Secretary General Pedro Ross Leal, it was reported that operations at the largest work shoe factory, located in Granma, are being affected by the lack of electricity, although the necessary raw materials are available. The CTC national secretariat acknowledged the work done by Granma Province, and pointed out that the metallurgy sector has grown 16 percent in the first quarter of 1994 and has reduced losses by 16 million pesos.
